diminution of body mass index, loss of muscle mass or quadriceps strength, 
dispense, anxiety, depression and quality of life. Different tools, such as the 
BODE index or its modifications which integrate the predictive value of several 
manifestations of COPD, are now validated for the estimation of life expectancy.
CONCLUSION: These new data are a further advance in the understanding of the 
disease and the optimisation of the diagnosis, evaluation and management of 
patients.

